{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 09:58:08.449848", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary of Network Health\\n- Fabric control plane: Healthy. All EBGP sessions are established across the Clos tiers.\\n  - Leaves (AS 65200/65201) have EBGP up to both spines, each receiving 1 prefix and advertising their local /24.\\n  - Spines (AS 65100/65101) have EBGP up to super-spine and to both leaves; both /24s are present in their RIBs.\\n  - Super-spine (AS 65000) has both /24s installed (best path via spine 0_0).\\n- Inter-router links (/31s) are up and passing traffic.\\n- Leaf–host L2 links are up, ARP works in both directions.\\n\\nObserved Anomalies\\n- End-to-end host connectivity between pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24) and pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24) fails:\\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 ping: timeouts.\\n  - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0 ping: timeouts.\\n- pc_0_1 ↔ its gateway (leaf_router_0_1, 172.16.0.7/10.0.1.1): OK.\\n- pc_0_0 ↔ its gateway (leaf_router_0_0, 10.0.0.1): Fails for IP ping, but ARP succeeds:\\n  - From pc_0_0: arping 10.0.0.1 succeeds; ICMP echo to 10.0.0.1 times out.\\n  - From leaf_router_0_0: arping 10.0.0.2 succeeds; ICMP echo to 10.0.0.2 times out.\\n\\nKey Evidence\\n- Host configs:\\n  - pc_0_0: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1 (correct).\\n  - pc_0_1: 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1 (correct).\\n- ARP/neighbors:\\n  - pc_0_0 has 10.0.0.1 in ARP; leaf_router_0_0 has 10.0.0.2 in ARP (REACHABLE). L2 is functional.\\n- BGP routes:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0: B>* 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: B>* 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6\\n  - spines and super-spine have both /24s installed. Control plane is converged.\\n- Firewall on pc_0_0:\\n  - iptables (legacy) and nftables show an OUTPUT chain rule that drops virtually all IP egress:\\n    - iptables: -A OUTPUT -m length --length 10:65535 -j DROP\\n    - nftables: table ip filter, chain OUTPUT: meta length 10-65535 drop\\n  - sysctl shows ICMP echo ignore disabled; rp_filter disabled. No INPUT chain blocking observed.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- The failure localizes to pc_0_0 (host side), not the fabric:\\n  - ARP functions both ways (rules out L2/link issues).\\n  - Leaf cannot receive ICMP replies from pc_0_0 (ping leaf→host fails), consistent with pc_0_0 OUTPUT chain dropping responses.\\n  - pc_0_0 cannot originate IP packets to its gateway or to pc_0_1 (ping host→leaf/host fails), consistent with OUTPUT chain drop.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Misconfigured firewall on pc_0_0: An OUTPUT chain rule drops all IP packets with length 10–65535 bytes, which includes standard ICMP echo requests and replies (and most IP traffic). This prevents pc_0_0 from sending any IP traffic off-host and from replying to probes, despite ARP/L2 and routing being correct.\\n\\nImpact\\n- All IP connectivity to/from pc_0_0 is effectively blocked at the host’s egress. The fabric itself is healthy and correctly routes both /24 prefixes., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='d7893d43-1e70-4e23-9661-1ef49c43f0ff'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
